The Top 10 Largest Malls in the USA are both a feat in terms of construction size and scope as well as a testament to the grandiose nature of the shopping experience in the USA. We have arranged the list of the top 10 largest malls in the USA based on the total leasable area. Malls across the world have become the trend in urban centers as shoppers demand a wider repertoire in their shopping experience. The USA has led this trend so here is the list of the top 10 largest malls in the USA Also Read: Top ten largest airports in the USA Mall of America (MOA) is the largest mall in America. It is situated southeast of the junction of Interstate 494 and Minnesota State Highway 77, north of the Minnesota River, and across the Interstate from the Minneapolis St. Paul International Airport, in Bloomington, a suburb of the Twin Cities in Minnesota. Managed by the Triple Five Group, a multinational diversified conglomerate, development, and Finance Corporation with offices in the major U.S., Canadian and global cities. The mall was opened in 1992 and it has a total of 5,600,000 square feet (520,000 m2) of retail space setting it way ahead in the list of top 10 largest malls in America. Currently, the Mall of America features more than 520 retail stores, 50 restaurants, and the country’s largest indoor theme park, an aquarium with 100 sharks and 4,500 sea creatures, two on-site hotels, and a mouth-watering culinary scene.  Located in the Meadowlands Sports Complex in East Rutherford, New Jersey, American Dream is a retail and entertainment complex that consists of 70% entertainment facilities and 30% retail locations. Opened in phases starting from 2019, the mall has a total retail space of 3,000,000 square feet (280,000 m2) and it features 450+ stores, food and specialty shops, and six distinctive grand atriums with Nickelodeon Universe – an indoor theme park and two miniature 18-hole golf courses and Sea Life Minnesota Aquarium that displays over 4,500 fish and marine animals, including 100 sharks just to mention a few. American Dream is owned and managed by Triple Five Group.  King of Prussia, also referred to as King of Prussia Mall is a shopping mall located in the community of King of Prussia in Upper Merion Township in the United States state of Pennsylvania. With 2,793,200 square feet (259,500 m2) of retail space, the mall comprises seven major department stores and more than 450 stores, boutiques, and restaurants. The mall is owned and managed by Simon Property Group, Inc., an American real estate investment trust that invests in shopping malls, outlet centers, and community/lifestyle centers.  With a total of 2,738,730 square feet (254,436 m2) of gross leasable area, South Coast Plaza is a regional shopping mall located in Costa Mesa, a city in Orange County, California. The mall, which was opened back in 1967, has more than 250 luxury and fashion boutiques, 30 restaurants, and the adjacent celebrated Segerstrom Center for Arts. With a total of 24 million visitors annually, it is the largest shopping mall in California and the fourth on our list. South Coast Plaza is owned by C J Segerstrom & Sons, a family business incorporated as a real estate company in Orange County (along with the Irvine Company and the O’Neill family), especially in the city of Costa Mesa.  Opened in 1983, by Simon Property Group, a global leader in the ownership of premier shopping, dining, entertainment, and mixed-use destinations and an S&P 100 company (Simon Property Group, NYSE: SPG)., in partnership with Turnberry Associates, a Donald Soffer and family-owned company that develops real estate in the United States, Aventura Mall is an upscale shopping mall located in Aventura, a planned, suburban city in northeastern Miami-Dade County, Florida. The mall has 2,700,000 square feet (250,000 m2) of leasable retail space and it features a mix of over 300 stores, more than 50 eateries and restaurants, including a treats food hall, and the experiential arts Aventura Mall program showcasing 20 museum-quality pieces in a range of mediums.  Del Amo Fashion Center is a three-level regional shopping mall located in Torrance, a city in the Los Angeles metropolitan area, Los Angeles County, California. With a gross leasable area of 2,517,765 sq. ft. (233,908 m2), the mall has more than 200 stores that include Michale Kors, Hugo Boss, Arhaus Furnishings, lululemon, J. Crew, Madewell, Zara, Adidas, H&M, Express, Forever 21, and Marshalls and numerous dining options. Opened back in 1961, Del Amo Fashion Center is currently managed and co-owned by Simon Property Group, JPMorgan Fleming Funds (25%), and Farallon Cap. Mgt. (25%).  Serving more than 24 million visitors annually, The Galleria, stylized the Galleria and also known as the Houston Galleria, is an upscale mixed-use urban development and shopping mall located in the Uptown District of Houston, Texas. The mall has a gross leasable area of 2,400,838 square feet (223,045.1 m2), and it consists of a retail complex with a total of 400 stores and restaurants, as well as three office towers (Galleria Office Towers complex), two high-rise hotels (Westin hotels), and a private health club. It was opened in 1970 and it is owned by Simon Property Group (50.4%), Walton Street Real Estate Funds, Sony Corporation & CalPERS.  Stylized as destiny usa and formerly known as Carousel Center, Destiny USA is a six-story, automobile-oriented super-regional shopping, and entertainment complex on the shore of Onondaga Lake in the city of Syracuse, New York. The mall was opened on October 15, 1990, and it has six above-ground floors and one underground floor. The lower three floors and the underground floor are used for retail shops while the first and second floors house the various shops, vendors, restaurants, and entertainment venues, with the major food court and namesake carousel located on the second floor. The third floor on the other hand includes 19-screen Regal Cinemas, restaurants, and entertainment options while the fourth floor is primarily administrative offices. The underground floor, known as the Commons floor, houses medium-sized stores, a chapel, kiosks, and two underground parking garages. Destiny USA has a gross leasable area of 2,400,000 square feet (220,000 m2) and it is owned by Pyramid Management Group, the largest privately-held shopping mall developer in the Northeast, owning, leasing, and operating 15 shopping centers.  Roosevelt Field is located adjacent to the Meadowbrook State Parkway in Garden City, Nassau County, on Long Island, New York. Roosevelt Field is a shopping mall with a total of 2,366,692 square feet (219,872.9 m2) of the leasable area making it rank in the list of largest malls in America. The mall is managed and owned by Simon Property Group, and it has a total of 294 stores. Opened in 1956, which makes it the oldest mall on our list, Roosevelt Field is reportedly the second most successful mall in the state with tenants such as Bloomingdale’s, JCPenney, Macy’s, Nordstrom, Dick’s Sporting Goods, and Neiman Marcus. Owned by Simon Property Group, Sawgrass Mills is an outlet shopping mall located in Sunrise, Florida within the Miami-Fort Lauderdale-West Palm Beach metropolitan area. The mall ranks number 10 in the list of the top 10 largest malls in America.  Opened back in 1990 as the third mall developed by the now-defunct Mills Corporation, the mall currently has 2,273,898 square feet (211,252.0 m2) of the leasable area making it the largest shopping mall in Broward County, the second-largest in Florida and the Miami metropolitan area after the Aventura Mall, the third-largest in the southeastern United States and the tenth-largest in the entire country. Sawgrass Mills has more than 350 stores, including outlet locations from Nike, Tommy Hilfiger, Ralph Lauren, and Gap, plus value retailers OFF 5th Saks Fifth Avenue, Bed Bath & Beyond, Target, Marshalls, and electronics superstore, BrandsMart USA50. It also has two food courts, dozens of grab-and-go options, and 15 full-service restaurants in addition to “In the Game” Restaurant and Arcade, complete with state-of-the-art games, simulators, and a full restaurant and bar. 